    "content": "Add a permanent home alias in WSL2 Vim\nvim ~/.bashrc alias home='cd /mnt/c/Users/david.thomas$' \u003c--- Add this line to file, not a command. $ source ~/.bashrcYank entire file to clipboard in vim sudo apt install vim-gtk3 # open vim :%y+Create new user with . in the name add user --force-badname david.thomasand add them to sudoer file\nsudo usermod -aG sudo david.thomasCreate and edit- /etc/wsl.conf Ceate a /etc/wsl.conf with the following setting:\n[user] default=usernameChanging, of course, username to be your default username.\nExit your distro/instance, then issue a wsl --terminate \u003cdistroname\u003e from PowerShell or CMD. When you restart, the default user should be set.\nThis is safer and less error-prone than the registry-based methods.02\n",
